pageContext.claim: “When our country is assaulted by thousands and thousands of people marching, and they openly say we're going to go into the country, we can't do that. We can't do that. We can't allow that.”
pageContext.analysis: The migrants from Honduras, originally said to be 7,000 but quickly dwindling, were more than 1,000 miles away when Trump claimed the country was being assaulted.
